    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-04-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-04-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="343"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d343">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.515/15</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chief of the Financial Division</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Livesey</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Financial Counselor of the British
                        Embassy</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stopford</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-04">April 4,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Stopford</hi>: The Department has carefully
                    considered the suggestion in your letter of March 17, 1942<note n="28"
                        xml:id="d343fn28">Not printed; for substance of letter, see telegram No. 75,
                        March 23, 11 p.m., to the Minister in Iran, <ref target="#pg_300">p.
                            300</ref>.</note> that the United States Minister in Tehran be
                    authorized to support the British Minister <pb facs="0314" n="302"
                        xml:id="pg_302"/> in resisting an increase in the pound sterling value of
                    the rial. It does not appear to the Department, however, that our intervention
                    with the Iranian authorities with regard to this matter would be advisable at
                    this time.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Frederick Livesey</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
